The paper deals with using deep learning methods to predict demographic information from mobile phone metadata. This falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it involves studying human behavior at a large scale. The use of deep learning methods also suggests that it could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with data mining (cs.SD) as it involves extracting useful information from large datasets. The use of convolutional networks suggests that it could fall under the category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CY). Finally, the paper deals with privacy and security (cs.CR) as it involves the use of personal data.
